<br/>  


Supervised learning for factor investing
================
This page contains teaching material (**R** code) for **introductory** courses on supervised learning applied to factor investing.   

$\rightarrow$ The slides are available upon request.

------------------------------------------------------------------------


Sessions
----

The links below lead to **html** notebooks. The original **Rmd** files can be downloaded below.

1.  <a href="files/S1_Foundations.nb.html" target="_blank">**Economic foundations**</a>: asset pricing anomalies, characteristics-based investing.

2.  <a href="files/S2_Portfolio.nb.html" target="_blank">**Portfolio strategies**</a>: portfolio backtesting framework.

3.  <a href="files/S3_Lasso.nb.html" target="_blank">**LASSO & Sparse portfolios**</a>: penalised regressions for minimumn variance portfolios and for robust predictive forecasts.

4.  <a href="files/S4_Data.nb.html" target="_blank">**Data preparation**</a>: Feature engineering and labelling with a focus on categorical data.

5.  <a href="files/S5_Trees.nb.html" target="_blank">**Decision trees**</a>: Simple trees, random forests and boosted trees.

6.  <a href="files/S6_NN.nb.html" target="_blank">**Neural networks**</a>: Multilayer perceptron and recurrent networks (**G**ated **R**ecurrent **U**nits). 

7.  <a href="files/S7_Validation.nb.html" target="_blank">**Validating & tuning**</a>: performance metrics and hyper-parameter adjustment. 

8.  <a href="files/S8_Extensions.nb.html" target="_blank">**Extensions**</a> : SVMs, ensemble learning, interpretability and deflated Sharpe ratios. 


 

---------------------------------


Datasets (in R format):
----------

<a href="https://github.com/shokru/coqueret.github.io/blob/master/files/data.RData" target="_blank">**Base**</a>: 30 firms, 6 features;  
<a href="https://github.com/shokru/coqueret.github.io/blob/master/files/data_full.RData" target="_blank">**Large**</a>: 200+ firms, 10 features.  


------------------------------------------------------------------------

**DISCLAIMER**: the **data** and **code** are meant for pedagogical use only. 

